Instead, Treat Angel allows members to choose any item from www.treatangel.com free of charge each month, and just pay for shipping. Treats include fashion accessories & clothing, jewelry, cosmetics, items for the home, and treats for men & kids. More vertical sectors will be added as the business grows. Treat Angel partners with high-end retail brands who share the company's philosophy that life can be tough, and everyone deserves a treat. The heart at the center of Treat Angel's logo represents the company's pledge to bring a smile to people's faces on a regular basis: its members, its employees and some of those who are not in a position to treat themselves.

Description: Bobby Bear Fun & Fitness, Inc. (Bobby Bear) is a mobile fitness unit that creates a fitness and nutrition curriculum for children.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Bobby Bear Fun & Fitness, Inc. (Bobby Bear) is a mobile fitness unit that creates a fitness and nutrition curriculum for children at daytime childcare facilities, park districts, fitness facilities and local schools.  Bobby Bear's curriculum is designed to attack the staggering upward trend of childhood diabetes and obesity.  Bobby Bear's program travels to each individual facility and provides certified, background checked front line instructors, who are equipped with a Bobby Bear Box.  The Bobby Bear Box includes all equipment for exercise: the daily curriculum, first aid supplies and everything else necessary to provide proper instruction for the class.  Each class is approximately 30 minutes combining cardiovascular/strength/flexibility training, nutrition education and exercise words.  The child care facilities offer separate Bobby Bear classes for 2 year, 3 year, 4 year and 5 year old children.  The park district offers separate Bobby Bear classes that combine 2-3 year, 4-6 year old children and allows the parents to be involved in class.  The local schools, ages 6-12 year olds, are provided with an interactive assembly that provides a unique curriculum to the entire staff and student body.  A set curriculum is provided to the school to ensure healthy habits are practiced for the entire school year.  Local fitness facilities use the 2-12 year old curriculum during the Bobby Bear classes as well.  Bobby bear  performs data collection on specific measurable outcomes, such as height, weight, waist, hip etc.  This data base is used to address our curriculum to make sure the results are consistently up to date and relevant.  The Bobby Bear mascot is a role model for the whole community and he has made several appearances to every facility that uses our curriculum.  Bobby Bear has been in several parades, started a 5k race, participated in a winter season event with other characters all with the purpose to inspire children and families to live a healthy lifestyle.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Education, Health Care, Sports

Description: Encore Energy Partners LP (ENP) is a limited partnership engaged in the acquisition
Headquarters Regions: Greater Houston Area, Southern US
Full Description: Encore Energy Partners LP (ENP) is a limited partnership engaged in the acquisition, exploitation, and development of oil and natural gas reserves from onshore fields in the United States. The Company’s properties and oil and natural gas reserves are located in four core areas: the Big Horn Basin in Wyoming and Montana; the Permian Basin in West Texas and New Mexico; the Williston Basin in North Dakota and Montana, and the Arkoma Basin in Arkansas and Oklahoma. As of December 31, 2010, ENP operated properties representing approximately 86% of its proved reserves. Its network of natural gas gathering systems permits it to transport production from its wells. On July 29, 2011, it consummated the acquisition of producing oil and natural gas assets in the Permian Basin of West Texas (the Purchased Assets). On December 1, 2011, ENP merged into a wholly owned subsidiary of Vanguard Natural Resources, LLC.
